      <head rend="italic align-center">
        <lb/>Thoughts in Health, </head>
      <l rend="hanging"><lb/><hi rend="dc(2)">W</hi>Hen ſickneſs ſhall aſſail my nobleſt <lb/>part, </l>
      <l><lb/>And ruſh impetuous on my <sic>throbing</sic> heart; </l>
      <l><lb/>When pain poſſeſs'd of ev'ry nerve appears, </l>
      <l rend="hanging"><lb/>And nought but paleneſs my fall'n viſage <lb/>wears; </l>
      <l><lb/>When ev'ry earthly wiſh ſhall fade away, </l>
      <l rend="hanging"><lb/>And death ſhall chill the ſtiff'ning coarſe to <lb/>clay, </l>
      <l><lb/>Do thou, great God! in that ſurpriſing hour, </l>
      <l><lb/>Suſtain my foul by thy almighty power: </l>
      <l><lb/>Let faith, let hope, let extaſy of love, </l>
      <l><lb/>Wing me to reach the bliſsful ſcenes above, </l>
      <l rend="hanging"><lb/>And join the choir where each thy glory <lb/>ſings, </l>
      <l><lb/>There let me hail—adore thee king of kings. </l>
    </body>
